Researchers from 60 countries found that 32.5% of amphibian species are at risk due to climate change and pollution.
Efforts are needed to protect habitats and breed threatened species.
A hospital in Australia, part of the Frog Decline Reversal Project, struggles due to lack of funding and an increase in sick frogs.
In Peru, public opposition halted mining operations to study water impact.
In Belgium, three smugglers were caught with 600 rare frogs.
Scientists warn of amphibian extinction due to environmental degradation and contaminants.
Urgent action is needed to save these vital species.
